# CODEOWNERS — GitHub auto-requests review from the listed owners on any PR that
# touches a matching path. Enforce it with a branch-protection rule on `main`:
# Settings → Branches → Require a pull request → Require review from Code Owners.
#
# SETUP: replace @alsoknownassecurity/maintainers with your real GitHub team
# (Settings → Teams) or a space-separated list of @handles. A PR author cannot
# satisfy their own code-owner review, so list at least two people / a team.

# Default owner for everything.
*                       @alsoknownassecurity/maintainers

# Security-critical surfaces — keep maintainer-gated even if review loosens
# elsewhere. The hooks ARE the security boundary; install.sh writes user configs.
/install.sh             @alsoknownassecurity/maintainers
/config/hooks/          @alsoknownassecurity/maintainers
/config/settings.base.json        @alsoknownassecurity/maintainers
/config/managed-permissions.json  @alsoknownassecurity/maintainers
/shared/lib/            @alsoknownassecurity/maintainers
/tools/                 @alsoknownassecurity/maintainers
/.github/               @alsoknownassecurity/maintainers
